item.title: 首页
item.dc:creator: lailailailion
item.content:encoded:
Enjoy our culinary experience

我们不仅烹制美食，我们还为食客提供美好的就餐体验。Maywood 坚信美食应该独具特色，我们所做的一切都是为了践行这一信念。

查看我们的菜单

我们的故事

欢迎光临 Maywood

本餐厅由主厨 Patron Joan Smith 和行政总厨 François Lemoine 携手创立，是海淀区最棒的餐厅之一。

法国本身的迷人风情激发了我们的创意和热情，启发我们设计出美味的招牌菜品。我们致力于以充满新意和创意的方式改造您喜爱的法国菜肴，并以此为傲。

浏览我们的菜单

我们的菜单汇聚了各种法国地区的美食，而且会根据季节变化进行调整。请务必询问每日特色菜！

查看我们的菜单

示例菜单

开胃菜

野蘑菇碎肉
红烧野蘑菇配海带和液氮
14.50 美元

主菜

阿尔萨斯葡萄酒焖鸡
雷司令葡萄酒烹制的鸡肉，搭配洋葱、蘑菇和香草
25.50 美元

甜点

南瓜蛋奶酥
配波本威士忌、肉桂和糖蜜酱
9.00 美元

item.content:encoded:
Tasty & Fresh Bakery
Our Bakery offers classic, scratch-made baked goods for every occasion. We believe in the goodness of real food, made from scratch. We source only the finest ingredients and hand-craft our baked goods daily.
Our bakery and store-front hours are Monday-Friday 8:30-6:00pm and Saturday’s 10:00-2:00pm. Our phone and order hours are Monday-Friday 8:30-3:00pm and Saturday’s 10:00-2:00pm. Whether you are searching for a special birthday cake or simply looking for a sweet ending to an everyday meal, The Cake Shop offers something for everyone. This is a one of a kind bakery, where the aroma of home-style baking weakens even the strongest will.
Today's Menu 6th Jan 2022 Delight in three layers of cake paired with two generous layers of filling. DeEtta's uses real buttercream, offers a variety of flavors and fillings, and tailors everything — from taste to design — to your personal preferences.
view menu

Danishes, muffins, and scones ... oh my! Start your morning off right with a sweet treat from our bakery. Need a little pick-me-up any time of day? Look no further than our delicious selection of cookies, brownies, macarons, eclairs, and other goodies.
There is nothing like the aroma and taste of freshly-baked bread. We use traditional methods (without additives or preservatives) to ensure the best taste and quality possible. You can find us working in the wee hours of the morning mixing, kneading, and making each loaf by hand.

item.title: Chocolate Berry Cake
item.dc:creator: vvgam
item.content:encoded:
Chocolate and strawberries are yum. Chocolate and raspberries are yummier. And chocolate and both strawberries and raspberries are the ultimate yummiest! Case and point, this delectable Chocolate Berry cake. I’ve got a brand new chocolate cake recipe and it’s oh so wonderfully fluffy with that rich moist chocolate flavour reminiscent of a devil’s food cake. Paired with a strawberry raspberry buttercream…this Chocolate Berry cake is plate-licking good.

Intense chocolate cake layers that are both fluffy and moist. Covered in a sweet whipped berry buttercream full of real berries. A delicate balance of rich chocolate and sweet berry that sings on the tastebuds. This chocolate berry cake is not only easy to make but will have both the chocolate lover and fruit lover rejoicing!

The ingredients
Agricultural products
1/2 cup Blackberries
1/2 cup Blueberries
1/2 cup Raspberries
Refrigerate ingredients
3 Eggs
condiments
11/16 cup Honey
Baking and seasoning
1 3/4 cup All purpose flour
1 1/2 tsp Baking powder
1/4 tsp Baking soda
1 1/4 cup Cocoa powder, Dutch process
1 1/2 cups Granulated sugar

item.title: 专业摆盘技巧
item.dc:creator: lailailailion
item.content:encoded:
食物展示是修饰、加工、摆放或装饰食物以增强其美感的艺术。

在准备食物的各个不同阶段，无论是绑肉或缝肉的方式、切肉或切菜所用的切割类型，还是盛菜所用的模具样式，主厨往往都会考虑食物的视觉展示。食物本身可以像精心制作的冰镇蛋糕一样进行装饰，上面有时装饰着极具观赏性的雕刻样式的食材，淋上酱汁，撒上种籽、粉末或其他配料，也可以搭配可食用或不可食用的配菜。

在将食物放入餐盘时，食物的摆放和整体造型叫做“摆盘”。一些常见的摆盘造型包括：“经典”造型，即主菜摆放在餐盘的前面，蔬菜或淀粉质食品放在餐盘的后面；各种食品“堆叠”在一起；或者将主菜斜靠或“搭叠”在蔬菜或配菜上。食品在餐盘上的位置经常使用时钟表盘来表示，六点钟是最靠近用餐者的位置。

要实现好的摆盘，甚至在某些情况下进行备菜时，一个基本规则是确保一道菜包含 5 个组成部分：通常放在 6 点钟位置的蛋白质类，放在 2 点钟位置的蔬菜类，放在 11 点钟位置的淀粉类，另外还有酱汁和配菜。

来自维基百科。

item.title: Motcha Cake
item.dc:creator: vvgam
item.content:encoded:
With a bite of this matcha cake roll, you feel like you're in a rolling tea farm, with the fresh aroma of the tea leaves on your nose. Perhaps enjoying a matcha dessert will allow you to use your imagination and experience this evocative taste.

When it comes to tea drinking, although our country has a long history of tea culture, we still need to learn from our neighbour Japan in the field of matcha. It is a good thing that many domestic tea companies are now introducing Japanese production processes in the form of partnerships, which not only improves our own production techniques but also gives matcha lovers more choices in the market.

Matcha cake rolls are a very classic matcha dessert and many dessert masters have come up with recipes that are easy to learn. However, it still takes some work to make the cake rolls a success. For example, you must first learn to make the original cake roll, and on top of that you can change the flavours, which you will find easy to do. This cake roll is essentially a chiffon cake slice, but it still has a few differences from a round chiffon cake. Cake rolls require whipped egg whites that are on the softer side, with more liquid added, and the final batter is a little more liquidy.

The ingredients
Agricultural products
10 g Matcha
Refrigerate ingredients
3 Eggs, large
Baking and seasoning
80 g Flour
90 g Sugar
Dairy products
40 g Butter
30 ml Milk
liquid
1 tbsp Water

item.title: Egg Tart
item.dc:creator: roxymicchi
item.content:encoded:
The Portuguese cream tart, also known as the Portuguese egg tart, is a small, buttery pastry tart, characterised by its burnt black surface (the caramelisation of the sugar when it is overheated). It is said to have been invented by the nuns of the convent of Geronimo in Lisbon, Portugal, in the 18th century at the latest, and began to be sold in secular bakeries in 1837, when it was called the Belin tart because of the location of the shop in the Belin district of Lisbon.
The earliest Portuguese tarts came from an Englishman, Andrew Stow, who, after eating the traditional pastry Pasteis de Nata in Belem, a city near Lisbon, in Portugal, decided to add his own twist to the traditional recipe and opened Andrew's Bakery on Macau's Coloane Island in 1989, where he created the popular Portuguese tart using lard, flour, water and eggs, as well as the British style of pastry.
In 1996, Andrew's marriage to his wife Marjorie broke up.
She left Andrew to start a new business, renaming the shop under her own name "Margarita's", and inadvertently set up shop in Hong Kong and Taiwan, creating a whirlwind of Portuguese tarts.
Authentic Margaritaville Portuguese tarts must be made by hand: the delicately rounded crust, the golden egg and the proportion of caramel are all carefully controlled by professional chefs to achieve a level of quality that is difficult to achieve with ordinary tarts. The base of a Margaritaville tart is like a freshly baked croissant, with a fluffy, crispy texture and a rich, creamy, egg-filled filling, which, despite its layers of flavour, is not too sweet.

The ingredients
Refrigerate ingredients
6 Egg yolks
Baking and seasoning
3 tbsp Cornstarch
1 cup Sugar
1/2 Vanilla bean
Breads and bakery goods
17 oz Puff pastry
Dairy products
1 cup Milk

item.title: Sliced Bread
item.dc:creator: blackzeno
item.content:encoded:
Sliced bread is a loaf of bread that has been pre-sliced with a machine and packaged for convenience, as opposed to the consumer cutting it with a bread knife. It was first sold in 1928, advertised as "the greatest forward step in the baking industry since bread was wrapped" By 1933, around 80% of bread sold in the US was pre-sliced, leading to the popular idiom "greatest thing since sliced bread".

As commercially sliced bread resulted in uniform and somewhat thinner slices, people ate more slices of bread at a time. They also ate bread more frequently, because of the ease of getting and eating another piece of bread. This increased consumption of bread and, in turn, increased consumption of spreads, such as jam, to put on the bread.

The ingredients
Baking and seasoning
2 1/4 tsp Active dry yeast
5 cups All purpose flour
2 tsp Salt
1/2 cup Sugar
Oil and vinegar
1/4 cup Vegetable or canola oil
liquid
2 cups Water

item.title: Croissant
item.dc:creator: roxymicchi
item.content:encoded:
Known in France as croissants de boulanger, this yeasted dough is layered with butter and given a succession of folds that create the distinctive profile of classic croissants. Light and airy and shatteringly crisp, with a deeply caramelized buttery flavor, these croissants are a labor of love that's absolutely worth the time.

Crescent-shaped breads have been made since the Renaissance, and crescent-shaped cakes possibly since antiquity. Croissants have long been a staple of Austrian, Italian, and French bakeries and pâtisseries. The modern croissant was developed in the early 20th century. In the late 1970s, the development of factory-made, frozen, preformed but unbaked dough made them into a fast food that could be freshly baked by unskilled labor. The croissant bakery, notably the La Croissanterie chain, was a French response to American-style fast food,and as of 2008, 30–40% of the croissants sold in French bakeries and patisseries were baked from frozen dough.

Croissants are a common part of a continental breakfast in many European countries.
